{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1777057460421,"sessionID":"ses_23f228ff5ffeiKfbDbSH2OaYg8","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_8setXGTkx35lxDD0Ro7fHcKZ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"category":"quick","command":"analyze-mode","description":"Retrieve MBTI search results","load_skills":[],"prompt":"Continue the previous search session and provide final results only. Report relevant workspace files, if any, related to MBTI, personality assessment, inference prompts, or casual conversational profiling. If none exist, say so clearly and mention nearest reusable artifacts.","run_in_background":false,"session_id":"ses_23f21a733ffecgcNUszEvo3U79","subagent_type":""},"output":"Task continued and completed in 2m 2s.\n\n---\n\nI've searched the workspace and identified the following relevant materials and reusable patterns for designing a casual-chat MBTI inference agent.\n\n### Relevant Workspace Files\n\n| File Path | Relevance | Summary of Content |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\tmp\\xuanhuan-novel-agent-workflow.md` | **High (Patterns)** | Contains a comprehensive \"Multi-Agent Workflow\" for creative writing. Specifically relevant is the **Agent Role Partitioning** (Section 4) and **Long-term Consistency Assets** (Section 5), which include `cast-ledger.md` for character states and `relationship-map.md`. |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\opencode-capability-skill\\SKILL.md` | **Medium (Architecture)** | Provides a guide for scriptable engineering runtimes and **native agent design**. It details how to use \"rule files\" as task inputs and how to register custom tools in OpenCode. |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\doubao-mirror-agent\\README.md` | **Medium (Implementation)** | References a \"Mirror Agent\" architecture with session persistence, event logging, and a \"design\" directory (located in `projects/`). This is a template for an agent that maintains state over time. |\n| `D:\\agent_workspace\\capability-library\\skill-library\\andrej-karpathy-skills\\CLAUDE.md` | **Low (Guidelines)** | General behavioral guidelines for agents to reduce mistakes (caution over speed, simplicity, surgical changes). |\n\n### Reusable Patterns & Findings\n\n1.  **Agent Role & Responsibility (from Xuanhuan Workflow)**:\n    *   **Pattern**: Separate \"Observation/Review\" from \"Generation/Update\".\n    *   **Application**: For an MBTI agent, one agent role could be the **Inference Reviewer** (analyzing chat history for personality cues) and another the **Persona Maintainer** (updating the inferred MBTI profile in a structured ledger).\n2.  **Long-term Asset Management**:\n    *   **Pattern**: Use a \"Canon\" or \"Ledger\" file (e.g., `cast-ledger.md`) to store the \"ground truth\" of an entity's state.\n    *   **Application**: Maintain a `user-personality-profile.json` or similar asset that is updated after each significant interaction, rather than re-inferring from scratch every time.\n3.  **Stateful Session Design (from Mirror Agent)**:\n    *   **Pattern**: Implement `session.json` and `messages.jsonl` for persistent memory.\n    *   **Application**: Use structured logging of \"inference events\" (e.g., \"User exhibited high [E] trait in message #45\") to track the evolution of the MBTI assessment.\n4.  **Verification & Rework Loops**:\n    *   **Pattern**: \"提案 (Proposal) -> 分析 (Analysis) -> 找问题 (Problem finding) -> 决策 (Decision)\".\n    *   **Application**: The agent should propose an MBTI type, search for contradictions in previous chat logs, and only \"finalize\" the inference once a confidence threshold is met.\n\n**Note**: No specific MBTI-specific datasets, assessment questionnaires, or inference-specific prompts (e.g., \"Analyze the following text for INTJ traits\") were found. However, the **Xuanhuan Novel Workflow** provides the most robust template for a multi-agent system that handles character/personality state management.\n\n<task_metadata>\nsession_id: ses_23f21a733ffecgcNUszEvo3U79\nsubagent: Sisyphus-Junior\n</task_metadata>\n\nto continue: task(session_id=\"ses_23f21a733ffecgcNUszEvo3U79\", load_skills=[], run_in_background=false, prompt=\"...\")","metadata":{"truncated":false,"prompt":"Continue the previous search session and provide final results only. Report relevant workspace files, if any, related to MBTI, personality assessment, inference prompts, or casual conversational profiling. If none exist, say so clearly and mention nearest reusable artifacts.","load_skills":[],"description":"Retrieve MBTI search results","run_in_background":false,"sessionId":"ses_23f21a733ffecgcNUszEvo3U79","sync":true,"command":"analyze-mode","model":{"providerID":"MoreCode","modelID":"gemini-3-flash"}},"title":"Continue: Retrieve MBTI search results","time":{"start":1777057337488,"end":1777057460420}},"id":"prt_dc0df107f002kgNmN9mDL1EEyr","sessionID":"ses_23f228ff5ffeiKfbDbSH2OaYg8","messageID":"msg_dc0dee2f2001ETaMRiJn48EuLV"}}
